  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Slice the <strong>chestnut mushrooms </strong>and chop any larger <strong>oyster mushrooms </strong>in half</p><p>Add the mushrooms to a large bowl with <strong>half </strong>of<strong> </strong>the <strong>Marmite</strong>, a drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>and a grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and gently toss it all together until the mushrooms are coated – these are your <strong>Marmite mushrooms</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1601540066210-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1601540066210-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1601540066210-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1601540066210-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1601540066210-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>Marmite</strong> <strong>mushrooms</strong> to a large baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-15 min until the mushrooms have started to caramelise and crisp – this is your <strong>Marmite</strong> <strong>mushroom 'bacon'</strong></p><p>While the mushrooms are cooking, peel and finely slice the<strong> shallots</strong></p><p>Peel and slice (don't chop!) the<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1601540085250-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1601540085250-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1601540085250-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1601540085250-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1601540085250-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced shallot </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min until starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1601540113273-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1601540113273-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1601540113273-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1601540113273-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1601540113273-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the<strong> linguine</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the<strong> </strong>pasta for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the linguine, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water </strong>and drizzle the pasta with a little<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Tip: The olive oil stops the pasta from sticking together!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1601540130566-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1601540130566-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1601540130566-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1601540130566-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1601540130566-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> and the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>Marmite</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>Marmite stock</strong></p><p>Once the shallots have started to brown, add the<strong> sliced garlic </strong>and cook for 2 min further until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>Marmite stock </strong>and<strong> half </strong>the<strong> crème fraîche </strong>to the pan and cook for 2-3 min further until a smooth sauce remains – this is your <strong>creamy Marmite sauce</strong></p>",
